725597f-a.title: Queens: 71st Street - Woodside Avenue
725597f-a.text:
41-66 71st Street, adjoining the N. W. corner of Woodside
Avenue, showing the yard in rear of a two-story dwelling at
the above address. Shown, too, are the rears of homes fronting
on 70th Street.
P. L. Sperr  May 5, 1928
NO REPRODUCTIONS

725598f-b.title: Queens: 71st Street - Woodside Avenue
725598f-b.text:
41-50 71st Street, west side, between Woodside and 41at
Avenues, showing the ''Red Men's Hall,'' also known as Leon
Trotsky's visiting place, where the Bolshevik leader frequent-
ed during his sejourn in New York. The sign over the doorway
reads: ''Half Moon Tribe Imperial Order of Red Men Meets Here.''
P. L. Sperr  May 5, 1928
NO REPRODUCTIO3S  Views 1, 2, 3
